     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "EntanglementEntropy[vec, {d1, d2, ...}, {k1, k2, ...}] returns the \
entanglement entropy in pure state vec between subsystem {k1, k2, ...} and \
the rest. The subsystems are assumed to be associated with the Hilbert spaces \
with dimensions d1, d2, .... EntanglementEntropy[vec, {k1, k2, ...}] assumes \
that the subsystems are qubits. EntanglementEntropy[expr, {k1, k2, ...}] \
assumes that expr is a ket expression for unlabelled qubits {k1, k2, ...}. \
EntanglementEntropy[expr, {s1, s2, ...}] assumes that the subsystems are \
specified by species {s1, s2, ...}.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, 
